sentences: Maria-Cecilia Simone Kelly (born May 7, 1997), known professionally as Rico Nasty, is an American rapper and singer from Maryland.
She rose to prominence in 2018 with singles such as "Smack a Bitch" and "Poppin".
While in high school, Rico Nasty began self-releasing content in 2014 and had released five solo mixtapes by late 2017.

This was followed by the collaborative mixtape Anger Management (2019) with long time associate Kenny Beats.

The singles "Smack A Bitch", "Poppin" and "Key Lime OG" gained prominence in early 2018; all of them meeting and exceeding 10 million YouTube views in that year.
"Smack A Bitch" was also ranked at No. 2 on The Fader's list of "The 100 Best Songs of 2018".
The aforementioned influx of popularity helped Rico Nasty catch the attention of Atlantic Records, where she signed and released her sixth mixtape and major-label debut, Nasty, in June 2018.
The mixtape's tracks, "Bitch I'm Nasty", "Countin' Up" and "Rage", were also ranked on lists of the best songs of 2018 by Paper, Highsnobiety and Pitchfork respectively.
Rico Nasty released the non-album singles and respective music videos for "Guap (LaLaLa)" in December 2019, as well as "Roof" in January 2019.

In April 2019, Rico and producer Kenny Beats released the collaborative mixtape, Anger Management, as a surprise release.

Rico Nasty released "Own It" as the second single from Nightmare Vacation on September 17.
